reviewText: Loved it. It was cute, and funny. I felt I was watching two rom com at once. Loved that there were two stories, at the same time. feels like love won twice. :) The plus was seeing Quintana Roo and the Mayan community, the jungle/underwater cave. I am glad I bought the movie.

The movie is really bad, and I am trying to say it on a way it does not offend or at least respect Amazon guidelines for reviews. As a production it lacks of structure. From the very beginning you notice that there is something wrong, poorly written, poorly acted, you will just loose your money. Whatever silly US movie is better that this one... And it is so sad to me, because there are so many good emergent directors and producers that would do magic with such opportunity.
Cute movie!  Takes a little time to get into, but if you stick with it awhile, it really grows on you!
Everything is so good, the places where the history develops, the people, everything!!!!

I enjoy Mexican films especially comedies but this one was not good. It was really cheesy, had an unrealistic but predictable story line, the female lead actress was obnoxious, and it plainly was not funny. Disappointed.
It is not suitable for european dvd players.

I love this movie! I also discovered it from Redbox and I'm so glad I decided to give it a try.  It's your standard rom com but wonderfully done.  The cinematography is beautiful and I loved seeing the forest scenery.  It was a lot funnier than I expected to be; there's a nice balance of obvious, slapstick-y comedic moments and comedic moments that are quieter and more subtle (which made them even funnier!).  Now that I own the DVD I've watched this movie again and again, it's awesome.
Great Movie, very funny! I've watched it several times and still laugh every time.

This movie is hysterical!  The actors all did an excellent job.  The storyline is like none other, new and refreshing.  The scenery is amazing.  I would dare call this a "chick flick", although my husband watched it with me and he liked it very much.

I'm always looking for Spanish language movies to improve my language skills.  I happened upon this one as I was browsing the Amazon videos. The trailer looked cute, so I decided to rent it.  It was great -- cute plot, funny, serious, all at once.
